main event: An unidentified flying object was reported in Upper Darby, Pennsylvania on September 6, 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as white, oval-shaped, and luminous,The object moved in a straight line at a slow speed and was visible for 2-3 minutes,The object was estimated to be 30-40 feet in diameter and at an altitude of 500-1000 feet,No sound was reported during the sighting,The sighting was investigated by USAF personnel who labeled it as unidentified.
